Question: Do you think strict gun control laws would reduce violent crimes?
Answer:
I believe that strict gun control laws can reduce violent crimes to some extent. These laws will limit access to guns and weapons which are likely to cause  magnificant damage. The level of violence may be reduced in this way even if conflicts occur. Nevertheless, guns and weapons are not the real cause of crimes. It is the hardly changeable human nature such as aggression and greediness and reality--scarcity, unlimited wants but limited resources that cause crimes